    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI would like an option in Neovim to automatically behave as if i pressed `<C-F>` whenever entering an input, such as `:`, `/`, `?`, LSP renames, or any other feature that uses the same abstraction. Manually pressing `<C-F>` each time is tiresome.\n\n`<C-F>` already works for searches, commands, and inputs, which suggests there is underlying logic unifying these input types. However, as a user, i don't have access to a unified API for that, or an option to affect that. I only see the fractured manifestations built on top of said abstraction and must manually work around each feature built on it.\n\nFor example, this autocommand works for `:` but does not work for LSP rename prompts:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"CmdlineEnter\", {\n  pattern = \":\",\n  callback = function()\n    vim.cmd(\"normal! <C-f>\")\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nOverriding Neovim's `input` function affects LSP rename:\n\n```lua\n-- Preserve the original input function\nlocal old_input = vim.fn.input\n\n-- Override vim.fn.input\nvim.fn.input = function(prompt, default, completion)\n  -- Call the original input function\n  local result = old_input(prompt, default, completion)\n\n  -- Optionally, automatically perform <C-F> in the prompt buffer\n  vim.schedule(function()\n    local buf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\n    vim.api.nvim_feedkeys(vim.api.nvim_replace_termcodes(\"<C-F>\", true, false, true), \"n\", false)\n  end)\n\n  return result\nend\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```lua\nvim.o.option_to_make_input_modal_by_default = true\n```\n\nWhy separate when same under hood. And if no same under hood, maybe we wait until made same under hood cuz why not same under hood if both similar.",
